work.description: I worked on the Trading Technology team as a Trading UI Engineer. My responsibility was to create new components and support all the trading platforms within firm. I specifically worked on a couple large projects which I spearheaded from start to finish. Some of the most notable projects I worked on were revamping/refactoring new order ticket and creation of a brand new app support alerts page

This was a continuation of my internship. However, during my fulltime role, I did more development on our OCR engine by adding specific customization based on our document classification. I also took on the responsibility of a performance engineer which lead to the responsibility of benchmarking our system for releases as well as working with business to scale our system for the new TD merger.

I worked on the document ingestion team which classifies documents that come into Schwab. During my time as an intern, I helped with the discussions of choosing our vendor through doing a POC. In that POC phase, I gathererd information on recognization rate, processesing rate, and usability of product for every vendor.
